ke.go.moh.oec.lib
Class MessageType

java.lang.Object
  ke.go.moh.oec.lib.MessageType

 class MessageType
extends java.lang.Object

Class that records the properties of a message type. This can be used to examine the properties of a message type for various purposes during message processing.

Author:
Jim Grace

Constructor to initialize all the fields of a message type.

Parameters:
requestTypeId - RequestTypeId of the request message, or 0 if this message is only used as a response
responseMessageType - MessageType of any expected response to this message, or 0 if this message is only used as a response
templateType - the type of XML message template used by this message.
rootXmlTag - The (HL7 V3) root XML tag that identifies this type of message when parsing
defaultDestinationAddress - The default message destination address (if any) for this message, otherwise null
defaultDestinationName - The default message destination address (if any) for this message, otherwise null
toBeQueued - Is this message to be queued for store-and-forward if it can't send immediately (true), or not (false)
